body:
In some cases `IPTools::signed*ImpactParameter*()`can return invalid result, in which case the existing code fills the histogram with NaN (0/0). This PR adds protection against it.

Tested in CMSSW_7_5_X_2015-05-12-2300. Only expected change is no NaNs in these two histograms (would be visible e.g. in `Mean()` if anywhere), e.g. limited matrix shows no difference.

@rovere @VinInn
